#compdef ingress-coap-client
# ============================================================================
# _ingress-coap-client — zsh completion for diwise's CoAP test client
# ============================================================================
#
# UPSTREAM
#   Repository : https://github.com/diwise/ingress-coap
#   Author     : Diwise AB  (Swedish smart-city / IoT consultancy)
#   License    : AGPL-3.0
#   Stars      : 3
#   Language   : Go
#   Module     : github.com/diwise/ingress-coap  (Go 1.21)
#   Build      : go build ./cmd/ingress-coap-client/  →  ingress-coap-client
#   Last push  : 2024-11-06
#
# WHAT IT IS
#   ingress-coap-client is the test/probe CLI half of the diwise/ingress-coap
#   project — its sibling daemon `ingress-coap` is a long-running CoAP
#   (Constrained Application Protocol, RFC 7252) ingress server that
#   receives binary telegrams from field-deployed water-meter devices and
#   decodes the proprietary regular / type-2 telegram formats (the
#   decodeRegularPayload routine in cmd/ingress-coap/main.go parses
#   timestamps, total volume in litres, monthly references, flow rate,
#   water temperature, delta-volume series, and battery level).  The
#   client is a small UDP-CoAP poster that dials the server at
#   `<host>:5683`, POSTs a hard-coded sample telegram to the `/coap`
#   resource, and prints the response — used by Diwise to smoke-test
#   ingress-coap deployments and as integration-test fixture support.
#
# CLI ARGUMENT GRAMMAR  (verbatim from cmd/ingress-coap-client/client.go
#                       Go stdlib `flag.StringVar` calls)
#   ingress-coap-client [-host HOST] [-timeout SECONDS]
#
#   Flags  (single-dash long form via the Go stdlib `flag` package):
#     -host <HOSTNAME>     Hostname or IP to the COAP server
#                          (default: empty → dials :5683)
#     -timeout <SECONDS>   Timeout in seconds (default: 5)
#
#   Behavior:
#     - Always dials UDP CoAP on port 5683 (hardcoded `<host>:5683`)
#     - Always issues `co.Post(ctx, "/coap", message.AppOctets, payload)`
#       with a hex-decoded sample telegram (regular water-meter format)
#     - Logs the response as structured JSON via log/slog
#
# AXIS / CORPUS POSITION
#   Direct dependency on `github.com/plgd-dev/go-coap/v3 v3.3.0` declared
#   in go.mod — the canonical Go CoAP server+client library maintained by
#   the plgd.dev IoT platform team (the de-facto reference Go CoAP
#   implementation, used in production by plgd-hub, the open Cloud-Native
#   Computing Foundation OCF cloud).  Uses:
#     udp.Dial("<host>:5683")    — UDP CoAP transport
#     co.Post(ctx, "/coap", message.AppOctets, payload)
#                                — REST-style CoAP request
#   Verified via:
#     gh api repos/diwise/ingress-coap/contents/go.mod
#       → github.com/plgd-dev/go-coap/v3 v3.3.0
#   This entry is the Go=115 leader bump that continues Axis 60
#   (CoAP IoT Protocol Library — THREE-SCORE AXIS LANDMARK) opened at R829
#   with Rust=coap-lite 0.4.0 (ryankurte/rust-coap-client).
#
#   No completion for `ingress-coap-client` ships with Apple zsh
#   (/usr/share/zsh/*/functions) or Homebrew zsh-completions
#   (/opt/homebrew/share/zsh/site-functions) — confirmed absent.
# ============================================================================

_ingress-coap-client() {
    _arguments \
        '-host[hostname or IP to the COAP server]:host:_hosts' \
        '-timeout[timeout in seconds (default 5)]:seconds:' \
        '(- *)-h[show help]' \
        '(- *)-help[show help]'
}

_ingress-coap-client "$@"
